question
Points M and N are equally distant from point O, but located on opposite sides of it, 
in opposite directions.
points
Write a function called oppositePoint that takes the number x (the coordinate of point M) as an argument and 
returns the coordinate of point N as the string "N (x)".

solution:

function oppositePoint(x){
     return x === 0 ? `N(${x})` : `N(${-x})`
}
